/21209407">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22422383/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=CT+and+MR+cholangiography%3A+advantages+and+pitfalls+in+perioperative+evaluation+of+biliary+tree&amp;author=T+Hyodo&amp;author=S+Kumano&amp;author=F+Kushihata&amp;publication_year=2012&amp;journal=Br+J+Radiol&amp;pages=887-896&amp;doi=10.1259%2Fbjr%2F21209407&amp;pmid=22422383">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">23.</div><div id="r23" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Aduna M, Larena JA, Martín D, Martínez-Guereñu B, Aguirre I, Astigarraga E. Bile duct leaks after laparoscopic cholecystectomy: value of contrast-enhanced MRCP. <em>Abdom Imaging</em> 2005;30(4): 480–487.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s00261-004-0276-2">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/15688109/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Bile+duct+leaks+after+laparoscopic+cholecystectomy%3A+value+of+contrast-enhanced+MRCP&amp;author=M+Aduna&amp;author=JA+Larena&amp;author=D+Mart%C3%ADn&amp;author=B+Mart%C3%ADnez-Guere%C3%B1u&amp;author=I+Aguirre&amp;author=E+Astigarraga&amp;publication_year=2005&amp;journal=Abdom+Imaging&amp;pages=480-487&amp;doi=10.1007%2Fs00261-004-0276-2&amp;pmid=15688109">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">24.</div><div id="r24" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Zimmitti G, Roses RE, Andreou A, et al. Greater complexity of liver surgery is not associated with an increased incidence of liver-related complications except for bile leak: an experience with 2,628 con